📌 Abstract

Efficient frequency allocation is a critical problem in modern wireless communication systems. Improper assignment leads to signal interference, reducing network quality. This project models 40 cell towers as a graph and applies the Graph Coloring technique using Backtracking to assign frequencies such that no two towers within 5 km share the same frequency. The objective is to achieve minimum frequency usage (chromatic number) while ensuring interference-free communication.

---

🎯 Objectives

• To represent cell towers as graph nodes
• To identify adjacency based on distance (< 5 km)
• To apply backtracking for optimal coloring
• To minimize number of frequencies used
• To ensure no interference between nearby towers

---

🌐 Problem Definition

Given:

• 40 cell towers
• Distance constraint: towers within 5 km interfere

Task:

Assign frequencies (colors) such that:

• Adjacent towers ≠ same frequency
• Total frequencies used are minimum

